Zinc acetate dihydrate, hexamine (HMTA), absolute ethanol, and sodium citrate were obtained from China National Pharmaceutical Industry Corporation Ltd (Shanghai, China). Chitosan (CS) (M.W. 100,000-300,000, deacetylation degree ≥95%) and chloroauric acid (HAuCl4·4H2O) were purchased from Sigma-Aldrich (St. Louis, USA). All chemicals used in this work were of analytical grade and were used without further purification. The sulphydryl modified 18-base oligonucleotide probe (probe ssDNA), target complementary sequence DNA (cDNA), one-base mismatched ssDNA, three-base mismatched ssDNA, and noncomplementary sequence DNA (ncDNA) were synthesized by Shanghai Sangon Biological Engineering Technological Co. Ltd. (Shanghai, China). All DNA sequences were artificial sequences and were synthesized using standard phosphoramidite chemistry and purified using reversed-phase HPLC. Their base sequences were listed as below:

Capture probe DNA (S1): 5′-SH-(CH2)6-TCT TTG GGA CCA CTG TCG-3′;
Complementary target to S1 (S2): 5′-CGA CAG TGG TCC CAA AGA-3′;
One-base mismatch (underlined) target to S1 (S3): 5′-CGA CAG TGG TCC CAA CGA-3′;
Three-base mismatch (underlined) target to S1 (S4): 5′-CGA CAA TGG CCC CAA CGA-3′;
Noncomplementary target to S1 (S5): 5′-GCA TCG AGC GAG CAC GTA-3′.

Yttrium oxide (Y2O3
), terbium oxide (Tb4O7
